  "text": "A framework such as this can be used to test moderation hypotheses in the context of the implementation of previously successful interventions to increase physical activity. In one investigation using this type of intervention (STRIDE; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] compared the effects of two 12-month long tailored non face-to-face interventions (print and telephone) with an exposure-matched health education control intervention on physical activity. At a 12-month follow-up, participants in the print-based intervention reported significantly more physical activity than either the phonebased or control interventions, suggesting that print-based methods may be more effective at increasing physical activity [CITATION_4] . This same print-based method is the approach we used here.",
